cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper deals with analyzing and comparing algorithms for multi-instance pose estimation, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new method for analyzing errors in algorithms, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the impact of instance attributes on algorithm performance, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper applies its technique to compare two leading methods for human pose estimation on a dataset, which falls under the scope of cs.MM (Multimedia).
